        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 6:48AM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 648 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fairport Harbor, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Painesville, Fairport Harbor, Geneva-On-The-Lake, Mentor, Willoughby,
Eastlake, Geneva, Madison, Perry, Mentor-On-The-Lake, North Perry,
Thompson, Grand River, and North Madison.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
